<div class="c230_7">
<div id="v230.7.1"><span class="H7692 s">Shiggaion</span><span class="H1732 s"> of David</span><span class="H7891 s">, which he sang</span><span class="H3068 s"> unto the LORD</span><span class="H1697 s">, concerning the words</span><span class="H3568 s"> of Cush</span><span class="H1121 s"> the Benjamite</span><span class="H1145 s"> †</span><span class="H3068 s">. O LORD</span><span class="H430 s"> my God</span><span class="H2620 s">, in thee do I put my trust</span><span class="H3467 s">: save</span><span class="H7291 s"> me from all them that persecute</span><span class="H5337 s"> me, and deliver</span> me: <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (words: or, business)</span></div>
<div id="v230.7.2"><span class="H2963 s">Lest he tear</span><span class="H5315 s"> my soul</span><span class="H738 s"> like a lion</span><span class="H6561 s">, rending <i>it</i> in pieces</span><span class="H5337 s">, while <i>there is</i> none to deliver</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (none…: Heb. not a deliverer)</span></div>
<div id="v230.7.3"><span class="H3068 s">O LORD</span><span class="H430 s"> my God</span><span class="H6213 s">, if I have done</span><span class="H3426 s"> this; if there be</span><span class="H5766 s"> iniquity</span><span class="H3709 s"> in my hands</span>;</div>
<div id="v230.7.4"><span class="H1580 s">If I have rewarded</span><span class="H7451 s"> evil</span><span class="H7999 s"> unto him that was at peace</span><span class="H2502 s"> with me; (yea, I have delivered</span><span class="H7387 s"> him that without cause</span><span class="H6887 s"> is mine enemy</span>:)</div>
<div id="v230.7.5"><span class="H341 s">Let the enemy</span><span class="H7291 s"> persecute</span><span class="H5315 s"> my soul</span><span class="H5381 s">, and take</span><span class="H7429 s"> <i>it</i>; yea, let him tread down</span><span class="H2416 s"> my life</span><span class="H776 s"> upon the earth</span><span class="H7931 s">, and lay</span><span class="H3519 s"> mine honour</span><span class="H6083 s"> in the dust</span><span class="H5542 s">. Selah</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.7.6"><span class="H6965 s">Arise</span><span class="H3068 s">, O LORD</span><span class="H639 s">, in thine anger</span><span class="H5375 s">, lift up</span><span class="H5678 s"> thyself because of the rage</span><span class="H6887 s"> of mine enemies</span><span class="H5782 s">: and awake</span><span class="H4941 s"> for me <i>to</i> the judgment</span><span class="H6680 s"> <i>that</i> thou hast commanded</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.7.7"><span class="H5712 s">So shall the congregation</span><span class="H3816 s"> of the people</span><span class="H5437 s"> compass thee about</span><span class="H7725 s">: for their sakes therefore return</span><span class="H4791 s"> thou on high</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.7.8"><span class="H3068 s">The LORD</span><span class="H1777 s"> shall judge</span><span class="H5971 s"> the people</span><span class="H8199 s">: judge</span><span class="H3068 s"> me, O LORD</span><span class="H6664 s">, according to my righteousness</span><span class="H8537 s">, and according to mine integrity</span> <i>that is</i> in me.</div>
<div id="v230.7.9"><span class="H7451 s">Oh let the wickedness</span><span class="H7563 s"> of the wicked</span><span class="H1584 s"> come to an end</span><span class="H3559 s">; but establish</span><span class="H6662 s"> the just</span><span class="H6662 s">: for the righteous</span><span class="H430 s"> God</span><span class="H974 s"> trieth</span><span class="H3826 s"> the hearts</span><span class="H3629 s"> and reins</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.7.10"><span class="H4043 s">My defence</span><span class="H430 s"> <i>is</i> of God</span><span class="H3467 s">, which saveth</span><span class="H3477 s"> the upright</span><span class="H3820 s"> in heart</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (My…: Heb. My buckler is upon God)</span></div>
<div id="v230.7.11"><span class="H430 s">God</span><span class="H8199 s"> judgeth</span><span class="H6662 s"> the righteous</span><span class="H410 s">, and God</span><span class="H2194 s"> is angry</span><span class="H3117 s"> <i>with the wicked</i> every day</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (judgeth…: or, is a righteous judge)</span></div>
<div id="v230.7.12"><span class="H7725 s">If he turn</span><span class="H3913 s"> not, he will whet</span><span class="H2719 s"> his sword</span><span class="H1869 s">; he hath bent</span><span class="H7198 s"> his bow</span><span class="H3559 s">, and made it ready</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.7.13"><span class="H3559 s">He hath also prepared</span><span class="H3627 s"> for him the instruments</span><span class="H4194 s"> of death</span><span class="H6466 s">; he ordaineth</span><span class="H2671 s"> his arrows</span><span class="H1814 s"> against the persecutors</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.7.14"><span class="H2254 s">Behold, he travaileth</span><span class="H205 s"> with iniquity</span><span class="H2029 s">, and hath conceived</span><span class="H5999 s"> mischief</span><span class="H3205 s">, and brought forth</span><span class="H8267 s"> falsehood</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.7.15"><span class="H3738 s">He made</span><span class="H953 s"> a pit</span><span class="H2658 s">, and digged</span><span class="H5307 s"> it, and is fallen</span><span class="H7845 s"> into the ditch</span><span class="H6466 s"> <i>which</i> he made</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (He made a pit: Heb. He hath digged a pit)</span></div>
<div id="v230.7.16"><span class="H5999 s">His mischief</span><span class="H7725 s"> shall return</span><span class="H7218 s"> upon his own head</span><span class="H2555 s">, and his violent</span><span class="H3381 s"> dealing shall come down</span><span class="H6936 s"> upon his own pate</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.7.17"><span class="H3034 s">I will praise</span><span class="H3068 s"> the LORD</span><span class="H6664 s"> according to his righteousness</span><span class="H2167 s">: and will sing praise</span><span class="H8034 s"> to the name</span><span class="H3068 s"> of the LORD</span><span class="H5945 s"> most high</span>.</div></div>
